  "prompt": "How do I learn SAP for free with a course completion certificate?",
  "response": "Learning SAP for free and obtaining a course completion certificate can be a bit challenging, but there are several resources and strategies you can use to achieve your goal:\n\n1. **OpenSAP**: SAP\u2019s own learning platform, offers free courses on various SAP topics. While many of these courses provide a record of achievement upon completion, you need to pass the final exam to get a certificate.\n   - Website: [open.sap.com](https://open.sap.com/)\n\n2. **SAP Learning Hub, Discovery Edition**: This edition is free and provides access to a limited set of learning resources, including eBooks and some online courses. While it may not offer certificates for all courses, you can still get valuable training.\n   - Website: [learninghub.sap.com](https://learninghub.sap.com/)\n\n3. **YouTube**: Many SAP professionals and training organizations offer free tutorials and courses on YouTube. While these may not provide certificates, they can be a valuable learning resource.\n   - Search for SAP tutorials and courses on YouTube.\n\n4. **Coursera and Udemy**: Sometimes these platforms offer free trials or free courses temporarily. You can earn a certificate upon completion if you manage to register during such promotions.\n   - Websites: [coursera.org](https://www.coursera.org/) and [udemy.com](https://www.udemy.com/)\n\n5. **LinkedIn Learning**: Occasionally offers free access to certain courses during promotions, and they can provide certificates upon completion.\n   - Website: [linkedin.com/learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/)\n\n6. **Community and Forums**: Participate in SAP forums and communities. Sometimes users share free resources, courses, and even opportunities for certification.\n   - SAP Community: [community.sap.com](https://community.sap.com/)\n\n7. **Non-Profit Organizations or Educational Institutions**: Some non-profits or universities offer free training programs in partnership with SAP. Check for any local opportunities.\n\nRemember, while free resources can be incredibly valuable, they may not always come with official certificates of completion. In some cases, investing in a paid course can be worthwhile for the official certification and recognition it brings.",
